								Spring Expression Language (SpEL)
								---------------------------------

Language Reference
------------------
	
	Literal expressions
	-------------------
	The types of literal expressions supported are
		- strings
		- numeric values (int, real, hex)
		- boolean
		- null
	- Strings are delimited by single quotes.
	
	- To put a single quote itself in a string, use two single quote characters.
	
	- Numbers support the use of the negative sign, exponential notation, and decimal points. By default real 
	numbers are parsed using Double.parseDouble().
	
	Ref: MainForLiteralExpression.java
	
	Properties, Arrays, Lists, Maps, Indexers
	-----------------------------------------
	- Navigating with property references is easy:
		- just use a period(.) to indicate a nested property value.
		- 
		
	Ref: MainForPropArraysListsMapsIndexerExp.java